I'll help you create a professional report using the `docx` library in JavaScript/TypeScript. I'll provide a comprehensive example that demonstrates creating a document with headers, footers, formatted tables, and embedded images.

```typescript
import { 
  Document, 
  Packer, 
  Paragraph, 
  TextRun, 
  HeadingLevel, 
  Table, 
  TableRow, 
  TableCell, 
  WidthType, 
  BorderStyle,
  ImageRun,
  Header,
  Footer,
  PageNumber
} from "docx";
import * as fs from "fs";
import * as path from "path";

function createProfessionalReport() {
  // Create a new Document
  const doc = new Document({
    creator: "Your Organization",
    title: "Professional Report",
    subject: "Comprehensive Analysis",
    keywords: ["report", "professional", "analysis"]
  });

  // Create Header
  const header = new Header({
    children: [
      new Paragraph({
        children: [
          new TextRun({
            text: "Professional Report",
            bold: true,
            color: "000000"
          }),
          new TextRun({
            text: "\t",
            size: 24
          }),
          new PageNumber({
            format: "current",
            align: "right"
          })
        ]
      })
    ]
  });

  // Create Footer
  const footer = new Footer({
    children: [
      new Paragraph({
        children: [
          new TextRun({
            text: "Confidential | Â© Your Organization",
            color: "666666",
            size: 20
          })
        ],
        alignment: "center"
      })
    ]
  });

  // Document Structure
  const document = new Document({
    headers: { default: header },
    footers: { default: footer },
    sections: [{
      children: [
        // Title
        new Paragraph({
          heading: HeadingLevel.TITLE,
          children: [
            new TextRun({
              text: "Comprehensive Business Analysis Report",
              color: "003366",
              size: 36,
              bold: true
            })
          ],
          alignment: "center"
        }),

        // Subtitle
        new Paragraph({
          heading: HeadingLevel.SUBTITLE,
          children: [
            new TextRun({
              text: "Quarterly Performance Review",
              color: "666666",
              size: 24
            })
          ],
          alignment: "center"
        }),

        // Section Heading
        new Paragraph({
          heading: HeadingLevel.HEADING_1,
          children: [
            new TextRun({
              text: "Key Performance Metrics",
              color: "003366",
              bold: true
            })
          ]
        }),

        // Embedded Image
        new Paragraph({
          children: [
            new ImageRun({
              data: fs.readFileSync(path.resolve("./performance-chart.png")),
              transformation: {
                width: 500,
                height: 300
              }
            })
          ],
          alignment: "center"
        }),

        // Formatted Table
        new Table({
          width: {
            size: 100,
            type: WidthType.PERCENTAGE
          },
          rows: [
            // Header Row
            new TableRow({
              children: [
                new TableCell({
                  children: [new Paragraph("Metric")],
                  shading: { fill: "E0E0E0" }
                }),
                new TableCell({
                  children: [new Paragraph("Q1 Value")],
                  shading: { fill: "E0E0E0" }
                }),
                new TableCell({
                  children: [new Paragraph("Q2 Value")],
                  shading: { fill: "E0E0E0" }
                })
              ]
            }),
            // Data Rows
            new TableRow({
              children: [
                new TableCell({ children: [new Paragraph("Revenue")] }),
                new TableCell({ children: [new Paragraph("$1,250,000")] }),
                new TableCell({ children: [new Paragraph("$1,500,000")] })
              ]
            }),
            new TableRow({
              children: [
                new TableCell({ children: [new Paragraph("Expenses")] }),
                new TableCell({ children: [new Paragraph("$900,000")] }),
                new TableCell({ children: [new Paragraph("$850,000")] })
              ]
            })
          ],
          borders: {
            insideHorizontal: { style: BorderStyle.SINGLE, size: 1, color: "000000" },
            insideVertical: { style: BorderStyle.SINGLE, size: 1, color: "000000" },
            top: { style: BorderStyle.SINGLE, size: 1, color: "000000" },
            bottom: { style: BorderStyle.SINGLE, size: 1, color: "000000" },
            left: { style: BorderStyle.SINGLE, size: 1, color: "000000" },
            right: { style: BorderStyle.SINGLE, size: 1, color: "000000" }
          }
        }),

        // Conclusion Paragraph
        new Paragraph({
          children: [
            new TextRun({
              text: "Conclusion: ",
              bold: true
            }),
            new TextRun({
              text: "The quarterly performance shows significant improvement in key metrics."
            })
          ]
        })
      ]
    }]
  });

  // Generate the Word document
  Packer.toBuffer(document).then((buffer) => {
    fs.writeFileSync("Professional_Report.docx", buffer);
    console.log("Document created successfully!");
  });
}

// Run the report creation
createProfessionalReport();
```

### Key Features Demonstrated:
1. **Headers and Footers**
   - Custom header with document title and page number
   - Footer with confidentiality notice

2. **Formatted Content**
   - Heading levels (Title, Subtitle, Section Headings)
   - Text formatting (color, size, bold)
   - Paragraph alignment

3. **Embedded Images**
   - Inserting a performance chart image
   - Controlling image size and positioning

4. **Professional Table**
   - Percentage-width table
   - Styled header row
   - Bordered data rows
   - Metrics presentation

### Prerequisites:
- Install dependencies: `npm install docx`
- Ensure you have a `performance-chart.png` in the same directory (or modify the image path)

### Usage Notes:
- Customize text, colors, and content as needed
- Replace placeholder text and image with your actual data
- Adjust formatting to match your organization's style guide

### Recommendations:
- Use high-quality, professional images
- Maintain consistent color scheme
- Proofread all text carefully
- Consider adding more sections or details as required

The script generates a professional, well-formatted Word document with a comprehensive structure suitable for business reports, academic papers, or professional presentations.
